				<div id="attachment_16179" class="wp-caption alignright" style="width: 310px"><a href="http://sidelionreport.com/2012/10/03/become-a-sidelion-report-writer/nfl-detroit-lions-at-denver-broncos-8/" rel="attachment wp-att-16179"><img class="size-medium wp-image-16179" title="NFL: Detroit Lions at Denver Broncos" src="http://cdn.fansided.com/wp-content/blogs.dir/53/files/2012/10/5671208-300x194.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="194" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Oct 30, 2011; Denver, CO, USA; Members of the Detroit Lions huddle up before the start of the game against the Denver Broncos at Sports Authority Field. The Lions defeated the Broncos 45-10. Mandatory Credit: Ron Chenoy-US PRESSWIRE</p></div>
<p>The Detroit Lions are looking to put together a winning team for the 2013 season and I want to do the same thing here at SideLion Report. We didn&#8217;t take a step back in 2012 but we take the same &#8220;always looking to improve&#8221; philosophy. That means there is always room for talented writers looking for an outlet to share their thoughts and opinions about the Lions, NFC North and the NFL.</p>
<p>Whether you&#8217;re a hardcore football fan looking for a hobby or have aspirations of making sport writing a career, SideLion Report is looking to give you a chance. At this time we are specifically looking for people who can do at least one of the following&#8230;</p>
<ul>
<li>Cover breaking news and offer analysis beyond the obvious facts</li>
<li>Contribute at least one column in the same time slot each week</li>
<li>Engage with readers via SLR&#8217;s social media accounts</li>
</ul>
<p>If you&#8217;re interested and feel you can meet any of the threeÂ bullet pointsÂ above, <a href="http://fansided.com/join-fansided/">fill out an application</a> and specify how you would like to contribute to this site&#8217;s success. Accepted writers can be up and running very quickly so don&#8217;t delay!</p>
				
